<!-- Paperdoll configuration (Vanilla Vault Boy)
Provides metrics for the paperdoll on the Pip-Boy Stats and the HUD
WRITTEN BY AXONIS FOR VANILLA UI PLUS; MODIFIED SEPTEMBER 2022

For custom paperdolls, please install the Paperdoll Testbed from
www.moddb.com/mods/vanilla-ui-plus/addons/paperdoll-testbed and
follow its included PDF Readme. All of the following tags are meant
to be reviewed, except for the last one -->

<!-- Zoom and relative position of the head at the Pip-Boy -->

<_paperdoll_pipboy_scale> 1.45 </_paperdoll_pipboy_scale>
<_paperdoll_pipboy_x> 10 </_paperdoll_pipboy_x>
<_paperdoll_pipboy_y> 50 </_paperdoll_pipboy_y>

<!-- Alignment of the player name on the Pip-Boy in relation to the head -->

<_paperdoll_pipboy_name_x> 0 </_paperdoll_pipboy_name_x>

<!-- Zoom and relative position of the head at the HUD -->

<_paperdoll_hud_scale> 0.75 </_paperdoll_hud_scale>
<_paperdoll_hud_x> 0 </_paperdoll_hud_x>
<_paperdoll_hud_y> 40 </_paperdoll_hud_y>

<!-- Common metrics for both Pip-Boy and HUD

I've tried to match my paperdoll calculations with the those used
on the vanilla Pip-Boy Stats Menu (Menus\Main\stats_menu.xml).

For width and height try to use the smallest possible values to
allow precise hovering on the limbs at the Pip-Boy.
 -->

<_paperdoll_head_width> 85 </_paperdoll_head_width>
<_paperdoll_head_height> 92 </_paperdoll_head_height>

<!-- The position of the face is related (added) to the head -->
<_paperdoll_face_width> 48 </_paperdoll_face_width>
<_paperdoll_face_height> 64 </_paperdoll_face_height>
<_paperdoll_face_x> 14.5 </_paperdoll_face_x>
<_paperdoll_face_y> 16 </_paperdoll_face_y> <!-- the face is vertically aligned to the middle of the head -->

<!-- The position of the torso is related (added) to the head -->

<_paperdoll_torso_width> 102 </_paperdoll_torso_width>
<_paperdoll_torso_height> 128 </_paperdoll_torso_height>
<_paperdoll_torso_x> -14 </_paperdoll_torso_x>
<_paperdoll_torso_y> 86 </_paperdoll_torso_y>

<!-- The position of the limbs is related (added) to the torso -->

<_paperdoll_leftarm_width> 100 </_paperdoll_leftarm_width>
<_paperdoll_leftarm_height> 55 </_paperdoll_leftarm_height>
<_paperdoll_leftarm_x> 90 </_paperdoll_leftarm_x>
<_paperdoll_leftarm_y> 0.5 </_paperdoll_leftarm_y>

<_paperdoll_rightarm_width> 96 </_paperdoll_rightarm_width>
<_paperdoll_rightarm_height> 56 </_paperdoll_rightarm_height>
<_paperdoll_rightarm_x> -88 </_paperdoll_rightarm_x>
<_paperdoll_rightarm_y> -5 </_paperdoll_rightarm_y>

<_paperdoll_leftleg_width> 72 </_paperdoll_leftleg_width>
<_paperdoll_leftleg_height> 112 </_paperdoll_leftleg_height>
<_paperdoll_leftleg_x> 47.5 </_paperdoll_leftleg_x>
<_paperdoll_leftleg_y> 86 </_paperdoll_leftleg_y>

<_paperdoll_rightleg_width> 84 </_paperdoll_rightleg_width>
<_paperdoll_rightleg_height> 112 </_paperdoll_rightleg_height>
<_paperdoll_rightleg_x> -36.5 </_paperdoll_rightleg_x>
<_paperdoll_rightleg_y> 82.5 </_paperdoll_rightleg_y>

<!-- The position of meters are related (added) to the head -->

<_paperdoll_head_meter_x> 45 </_paperdoll_head_meter_x>
<_paperdoll_head_meter_y> -9 </_paperdoll_head_meter_y>
<_paperdoll_head_meter_dir> &center; </_paperdoll_head_meter_dir>

<_paperdoll_torso_meter_x> 37 </_paperdoll_torso_meter_x>
<_paperdoll_torso_meter_y> 120 </_paperdoll_torso_meter_y>
<_paperdoll_torso_meter_dir> &center; </_paperdoll_torso_meter_dir>

<_paperdoll_leftarm_meter_x> 150 </_paperdoll_leftarm_meter_x>
<_paperdoll_leftarm_meter_y> 78 </_paperdoll_leftarm_meter_y>
<_paperdoll_leftarm_meter_dir> &center; </_paperdoll_leftarm_meter_dir>

<_paperdoll_rightarm_meter_x> -70 </_paperdoll_rightarm_meter_x>
<_paperdoll_rightarm_meter_y> 74 </_paperdoll_rightarm_meter_y>
<_paperdoll_rightarm_meter_dir> &center; </_paperdoll_rightarm_meter_dir>

<_paperdoll_leftleg_meter_x> 100 </_paperdoll_leftleg_meter_x>
<_paperdoll_leftleg_meter_y> 220 </_paperdoll_leftleg_meter_y>
<_paperdoll_leftleg_meter_dir> &left; </_paperdoll_leftleg_meter_dir>

<_paperdoll_rightleg_meter_x> -30 </_paperdoll_rightleg_meter_x>
<_paperdoll_rightleg_meter_y> 220 </_paperdoll_rightleg_meter_y>
<_paperdoll_rightleg_meter_dir> &right; </_paperdoll_rightleg_meter_dir>

<!-- If you design custom icons for the top left notifications
(eg. when quicksaving), it's better to include them as loose files on
the "Textures\Interface\Icons\Message Icons" folder instead of drawing
them on the interfaceshared atlas which may be used by HD HUD mods. -->
<_paperdoll_loose_icons> 0 </_paperdoll_loose_icons>

<!-- Automatic resizer for HD paperdolls (override only if HD scaling fails) -->
<_paperdoll_HD_zoom> <copy src="globals" trait="_paperdoll_HD_zoom" /> </_paperdoll_HD_zoom>